cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with online tracking and privacy concerns. It could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it involves measuring tracking behavior across multiple countries and ISPs. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it addresses the societal impact of online tracking. The paper also involves the development of a browser extension, which could place it under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and the collection and analysis of large amounts of data, which could place it under cs.MM (Multimedia).
